      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">List-answer questions score near zero, in every arm.</strong> Extracting a complete multi-item set and citing it is the hardest sub-task here and the obvious next target — the same weak spot the FINMA report flagged.</p>
      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">French trails German</strong> (D: 42% FR vs 60% DE), tracking the training mix (271 DE vs 123 FR items). More balanced data closes it; the number is honest about where the model is weak today.</p>
      <p><strong class="font-semibold text-ink-900 dark:text-white">Format compliance is 71%, not 100%.</strong> The retrieval-aware fine-tune still drops the citation on some items — far better than the naive 16%, not perfect. It's a floor: a larger, more balanced training set moves it further.</p>
    </div>
